奥利弗·安东尼备受争议的乡村歌曲“Rich Men North Of Richmond”创造了美国排行榜历史https://www.nme.com/news/music/oliver-anthony-controversial-viral-country-song-rich-men-north-of-richmond-makes-us-chart-history-3486642?utm_source=rss&utm_medium= rss&utm_campaign=奥利弗·安东尼·有争议的病毒乡村歌曲富人里士满北部使美国图表历史Tom SkinnerTue, 22 Aug 2023 13:53:43 +0000 Music NewsNewsCountry https://www.nme.com/?p=3486642 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="奥利弗·安东尼现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>该曲目于本月早些时候发行</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oliver-anthony-controversial-viral-country-song-rich-men-north-of-richmond-makes-us-chart-history-3486642">奥利弗·安东尼 (Oliver Anthony) 备受争议的乡村歌曲《里士满北部的富人》(Rich Men North Of Richmond) 创造了美国排行榜历史，并</a>首次出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="奥利弗·安东尼现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/oliver-anthony-branded-offensive-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>乡村歌手奥利弗·安东尼凭借他最近备受争议的单曲“Rich Men North Of Richmond”创造了美国排行榜历史。</p><p>该歌曲于 8 月 8 日发行，此后在 iTunes 乡村音乐排行榜上名列第一，在 Apple Music 全球音乐排行榜上飙升至榜首，并在 YouTube 上获得了超过 3200 万次观看。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/who-is-viral-rich-men-north-of-richmond-singer-oliver-anthony-and-why-is-he-controversial-3485137">谁是病毒式传播的“里士满北部的富人”歌手奥利弗·安东尼？他为何备受争议？</a></strong></li></ul><p>该曲目现已在 Billboard Hot 100 排行榜上首次亮相，使安东尼（前工厂工人和农民）成为第一个没有任何先前排行榜历史的艺术家（来自<a href="https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/oliver-anthony-music-rich-men-north-of-richmond-number-one-debut-hot-100-1235396681/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> ）。</p><p>安东尼（真名是 Christopher Anthony Lunsford）是 Billboard 历史上第六位首次以个人身份首次登上 Hot 100 排行榜第一的人，紧随<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/zayn-malik">Zayn</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/baauer">Baauer</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/carrie-underwood">Carrie Underwood</a> 、Fantasia 和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/baauer">Clay Aiken</a>的脚步。</p><p>除了这一壮举之外，安东尼还以未签约艺人的身份罕见地登上了百强单曲榜第一名，并发行了自己发行的歌曲《Rich Men...》。</p><p> “我们这个时代的绝望和沮丧在人们对这首歌的反应中产生了共鸣，”他在登上百强单曲榜榜首后告诉<em>公告牌</em>。“这首歌本身并没有什么特别的，但支持它的人们是令人难以置信的，值得被听到。”</p><p> 《富人……》上映后受到包括丹·邦吉诺和马特·沃尔什在内的各种右翼媒体人物的赞扬。 Republication representative Marjorie Taylor Greene, meanwhile, <a href="https://twitter.com/RepMTG/status/1689987536511258624" target="_blank" rel="noopener">described</a> it as “the anthem of the forgotten Americans who truly support this nation and unfortunately the world”.</p><p> But other people have <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/viral-right-wing-country-song-rich-men-north-of-richmond-branded-offensive-and-fatphobic-3484428">criticised the single for being “fatphobic” and labelled it a “right-wing anthem”</a> . </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="奥利弗·安东尼 - 里士满北部的富人" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sqSA-SY5Hro?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Despite highlighting societal issues such as homelessness in the US and the nation&#39;s mental health crisis, the song sees Anthony punch down on the “ <em>obese milkin&#39; welfare</em> “. He sings that “ <em>if you&#39;re 5-foot-3 and you&#39;re 300 pounds/ Taxes ought not to pay for your bags of fudge rounds</em> “.</p><p> &#39;Rich Men…&#39; could in part be interpreted as a working-class anthem, as Anthony mentions “ <em>sellin&#39; my soul</em> ” for “ <em>bullshit pay</em> “, and lambasts politicians and the “ <em>rich men north of Richmond</em> ” who “ <em>just wanna have total control</em> “.</p><p> However, he takes an anti-taxes stance too. “ <em>&#39;Cause your dollar ain&#39;t shit, and it&#39;s taxed to no end</em> ,” he sings elsewhere.</p><p> According to <a href="https://www.luminategroup.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Luminate</a> , &#39;Rich Men…&#39; registered 17.5million streams and sold 147,000 downloads in the tracking week ending August 17. Additionally, the tune received 553,000 radio airplay audience impressions, the majority of which were on country stations.</p><p> The song is the first solo-written Number One on the Hot 100 since <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/glass-animals">Glass Animals</a> &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/glass-animals-make-us-chart-history-with-heat-waves-3092240">&#39;Heat Waves&#39;</a> , which was written by the Oxford band&#39;s frontman Dave Bayley.</p><p> It is also the first song by a solo male to start atop both the Hot 100 and Hot Country Songs at the same time. It&#39;s the second overall, after <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/taylor-swift">Taylor Swift</a> &#39;s &#39;All Too Well (Taylor&#39;s Version)&#39; opened at Number One on both charts in late 2021.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> No words… Thank you. <a href="https://t.co/UUFVfJQdab">pic.twitter.com/UUFVfJQdab</a></p><p> — Oliver Anthony (@AintGottaDollar) <a href="https://twitter.com/AintGottaDollar/status/1690860511816978433?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 13, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Anthony held his debut public concert in Currituck, North Carolina earlier this month off the back of the recent hype. “No words… Thank you,” he wrote, captioning footage of the performance and what appeared to be a packed-out crowd.</p><p> In a statement on social media (via <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/21/rich-men-north-of-richmond-us-chart-history" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>the Guardian</em></a> ), Anthony said he wasn&#39;t rushing into signing a record deal just yet.</p><p> “People in the music industry give me blank stares when I brush off eight million dollar offers,” he explained. “I don&#39;t want six tour buses, 15 tractor trailers and a jet. I don&#39;t want to play stadium shows, I don&#39;t want to be in the spotlight.</p><p> “I wrote the music I wrote because I was suffering with mental health and depression. These songs have connected with millions of people on such a deep level because they&#39;re being sung by someone feeling the words in the very moment they were being sung.”</p><p> Anthony continued: “No editing, no agent, no bullshit. Just some idiot and his guitar. The style of music that we should have never gotten away from in the first place.”</p><p> Draven Riffe – Anthony&#39;s co-manager, and the sole producer of &#39;Rich Men North Of Richmond&#39; – said “there was not a whole lot of planning involved” ahead of releasing the song.</p><p> “We just knew if we got the video out there, people were going to love the song and it would resonate with a lot of folks,” he added.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oliver-anthony-controversial-viral-country-song-rich-men-north-of-richmond-makes-us-chart-history-3486642">Oliver Anthony&#39;s controversial viral country song &#39;Rich Men North Of Richmond&#39; makes US chart history</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
